1882a284-5155-4d61-93a8-a05a7c7a4d39.000ab249-0b29-4057-bbfa-5b323c87e8bb.prompt=Select protocol\: 1882a284-5155-4d61-93a8-a05a7c7a4d39.0327f829-ca06-4850-bf3a-5ef6923094f1.prompt=Enter host\: 1882a284-5155-4d61-93a8-a05a7c7a4d39.0b93c390-68e7-4bcf-82cd-c6318949680c.description=
Runs a command and allows user to specify that it runs locally (in this case no port should be specified), via ssh, Global Shell, ROSH, Telnet, or RSH.

Input Parameters\:
host - hostname or ip address
port - port number for connecting to the host
username - username to connect as
password - password
protocol - the protocol used to run the command (can be one of ssh, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, local or WMI)
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete
command - the command to execute
arguments - the arguments to pass to the command
environment - specifies environment variables/values that need to be defined when running command
startDir - the path to the starting directory
pty - (true, false) whether to use pty
privateKeyFile - The absolute path to the private key file for remote host.
sasHost - the host we want to run the ROSH command on
sasHostUsername - the username used to run the ROSH command on sasHost
usernamePrompt - the prompt that when seen should send the username
passwordPrompt - the prompt that when given should send the password
outputPath - network accessible path used by the operation to store temporary files. If not specified it points to \\host\admin$\temp\'. If this     path is not accessible you should change it to use another share that the host local system account has write access to. By default, the path will have to be  changed on Windows 2000 systems

Responses\:
success - the command was executed successfully
failure - the command could not be executed

Extra Results\:
stdErr - the STDERR of the command
stdOut - the STDOUT of the command

1882a284-5155-4d61-93a8-a05a7c7a4d39.d16ae22a-59c0-498e-90f6-480950900112.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];

1882a284-5155-4d61-93a8-a05a7c7a4d39.description=
This retrieves memory metrics using top and swapinfo commands.  

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address  of the host to check
port - port number for connecting to the host
username - username to connect as
password - password
protocol - the protocol used to run the command (can be one of ssh, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, local or WMI)
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete
pty - (true, false) whether to use pty
privateKeyFile - The absolute path to the private key file for remote host.
sasHost - the host we want to run the ROSH command on
sasHostUsername - the username used to run the ROSH command on sasHost
usernamePrompt - the prompt that when seen should send the username
passwordPrompt - the prompt that when given should send the password

Responses\:
success - if the data was obtained
failure - if the data could not be obtained (typically due to a problem with credentials)

Result\:
the output of both commands

Extra Results\:
activeRealMemory - the number of megabytes of total physical memory for runnable processes.
activeVirtualMemory - the number of megabytes of total memory for runnable processes.
freeMemory - the number of megabytes of unused physical memory.
freeSwap - the number of megabytes of unused swap.
totalSwap - the number of megabytes of total available swap space.
usedRealMemory - the number of megabytes of total physical memory for all processes.
usedSwap - the number of megabytes of used swap.
usedVirtualMemory - the number of megabytes of total memory for all processes. 
outputAll - the output of both top and swapinfo commands
stdOut - standard output of the top command
error - standard error of the top command
stdOut2 - standard output of the swapinfo command
error2 - standard error of the swapinfo command
code - the return code of the swapinfo command
